The paper deals with the problem of finding a small hitting set in an infinite range space, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry and has applications in various fields such as machine learning and data analysis. The paper uses techniques from convex optimization and multiplicative weight updates, which are commonly used in the areas of algorithms and information theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
